{"cursor":"17250","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n'Myrmecophyte' (mÉrâ²mekâ¢ÉâfÄ«t; literally \"ant-plant\") is a plant that lives in a\nmutualistic association with a colony of ants. There are over 100 different\ngenera of myrmecophytes. These plants possess\nstructural adaptations that provide ants with food and/or shelter. These\nspecialized structures include domatia, food bodies, and extrafloral\nnectaries. In exchange for food and shelter, ants aid\nthe myrmecophyte in pollination, seed dispersal, gathering of essential\nnutrients, and/or defense. Specifically, domatia\nadapted to ants may be called myrmecodomatia.\n","linknr":319,"url":"Myrmecophyte","recorded":1362372970,"links":24,"instances":["biology","botany","botany","botany"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Myrmecophytes|","Ants","Mutualism (biology)","Botany","Plants","Agriculturally beneficial insects","Acacia"],"headings":["Mutualism","Structural adaptations of myrmecophytes","Types of ant-plant interactions","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/89/Pseudomyrmex_ferruginea_Ryan_Somma.jpg/220px-Pseudomyrmex_ferruginea_Ryan_Somma.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2a/Myrmecodia_tuberosa_BotGardBln1105k.jpg/220px-Myrmecodia_tuberosa_BotGardBln1105k.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/A-cornigera.jpg/220px-A-cornigera.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Cherry_petiole_glands.JPG/220px-Cherry_petiole_glands.JPG","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Afzelia_africana1.jpg/220px-Afzelia_africana1.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf1